- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and semantic parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach to learn translational correspondences. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with modeling the meaning of technical documentation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with translating high-level textual descriptions to formal representations in technical documentation. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper involves mining technical documents for parallel text-representation pairs.
